# Active Directory Home Lab


## Goal
Simulate a small enterprise Active Directory environment for hands-on system administration practice.


## Environment
- Windows Server 2022 (Domain Controller)
- Windows 10 Client
- Hyper-V virtualization


## What I Did
- Installed and configured a domain controller
- Created Organizational Units (OUs) for departments
- Added users and security groups
- Configured Group Policy Objects (GPOs)
- Joined client machines to the domain


## Skills Demonstrated
- Active Directory administration
- Group Policy management
- Windows Server installation
- Troubleshooting domain join issues


## Lessons Learned
- Importance of OU design
- GPO inheritance and troubleshooting
- Common AD configuration mistakes
